# agent-canvas — Project Specification

> A Claude Code channel plugin that gives a running session a live browser UI,
> driven by a watched JSON state file and connected via the Channels protocol.

For rationale behind every architectural decision, see [agent-canvas-why.md](./agent-canvas-why.md).

---

## What this is

A channel plugin that opens a browser tab alongside your Claude Code session. Claude writes `.canvas/ui-state.json` to update the UI. Users interact with the browser and those interactions flow back into the session as channel events.

**Core principle:** Claude doesn't need special tools or awareness of the UI. It writes a JSON file — something it already does. The plugin translates that into a live browser page. If the plugin isn't running, the file just sits there. Nothing breaks.

---

## What it looks like in practice

### Scenario: Approval flow

A deploy workflow needs human sign-off. Claude populates a diff summary and waits for a decision.

**`.canvas/ui-state.json`**
```json
{
  "version": 1,
  "title": "Deploy Approval",
  "layout": "stack",
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "status",
      "type": "html",
      "content": "<span class='badge badge-warning'>Waiting for approval</span>"
    },
    {
      "id": "diff-summary",
      "type": "markdown",
      "content": "## Changes\n\n- Added retry logic to payment processor\n- Fixed null check in auth middleware\n- Updated 3 test files"
    },
    {
      "id": "approval",
      "type": "html",
      "content": "<div class='card bg-base-200 shadow-lg'><div class='card-body'><h2 class='card-title'>Approve Deployment?</h2><p>These changes affect the payment and auth systems.</p><div class='card-actions justify-end'><button class='btn btn-success' data-input-event='approve'>Approve</button><button class='btn btn-error' data-input-event='reject'>Reject</button></div></div></div>"
    }
  ]
}
```

When the user clicks Approve, Claude receives a channel event:
```xml
<channel source="agent-canvas" event="custom" component_id="approval" event_name="approve">
User clicked approve
</channel>
```

Claude reads this, proceeds with the deploy, and updates the status badge to success.

