## Architecture

```
Claude Code session
  --dangerously-load-development-channels
  --channels server:./channel/index.ts
        │
        │ stdio (MCP channel protocol)
        │
┌───────▼────────────────────────────────┐
│        Channel Plugin (Bun/TS)         │
│                                        │
│  • MCP server over stdio               │
│  • Declares claude/channel capability  │
│  • File watcher on ui-state.json       │
│  • HTTP server (localhost)             │
│  • SSE endpoint for browser push       │
│  • /input endpoint receives user events│
└───────┬────────────────────────────────┘
        │ SSE (push rendered HTML)
        │ HTTP POST (user input)
        │
┌───────▼────────────────────────────────┐
│        Browser Tab (localhost)         │
│                                        │
│  • SSE listener re-renders on update    │
│  • DaisyUI + Tailwind for styling      │
│  • User actions POST to /input         │
└────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

### Claude → Browser

1. Claude edits `.canvas/ui-state.json`
2. File watcher detects the change
3. Plugin renders all components to HTML
4. Full rendered output is pushed to the browser over SSE
5. Browser replaces the component container with the new HTML

### Browser → Claude

1. User clicks a button or submits a form
2. Browser POSTs to `/input`
3. Plugin wraps the payload as a `notifications/claude/channel` MCP event
4. Claude receives it as a message in the session and responds

