## Contract 1: The State File

### Location

```
<project-root>/.canvas/ui-state.json
```

If `.canvas/ui-default.json` exists and `ui-state.json` does not, the plugin copies the default on session start. If neither exists, the plugin writes a minimal empty state.

### Top-level schema

```json
{
  "version": 1,
  "title": "Page Title",
  "theme": "dark",
  "layout": "stack",
  "components": []
}
```

| Field | Type | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `version` | `number` | `1` | Schema version for forward compatibility |
| `title` | `string` | `"agent-canvas"` | Browser tab title and page heading |
| `theme` | `string` | `"dark"` | DaisyUI theme name |
| `layout` | `"stack" \| "grid" \| "sidebar"` | `"stack"` | Top-level layout mode |
| `components` | `Component[]` | `[]` | Ordered list of UI components |

**Layout modes:**
- **`stack`** — vertical, full width
- **`grid`** — 2-column responsive grid
- **`sidebar`** — first component in sidebar (1/3), rest in main (2/3)

### Component model

Every component has these base fields:

| Field | Type | Required | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| `id` | `string` | yes | Unique identifier. Used as the DOM element ID for targeted swaps. |
| `type` | `string` | yes | Component type name. Unknown types are silently ignored. |
| `visible` | `boolean` | no | Defaults to `true`. Set `false` to hide without removing from state. |

Component types:

- **`html`** — raw HTML with full access to DaisyUI + Tailwind classes. The primary way to render visual UI. Any DaisyUI component (badges, alerts, cards, stats, progress bars, navbars, tabs, etc.) can be used directly.
- **`markdown`** — renders a markdown string as HTML. Supports raw HTML passthrough for embedded content (iframes, DaisyUI markup, etc.).
- **`form`** — structured input form defined as JSON fields. Submissions flow back to Claude as channel events. Exists as a typed component because forms need input binding, validation, and event wiring that would be error-prone to write as raw HTML every time.
- **`log`** — scrolling append-only log panel. Exists as a typed component because it has diff behavior — the renderer appends new entries without re-rendering the full list.

The component set is extensible — new typed components can be added when a pattern benefits from structured JSON over raw HTML.

