## Contract 2: Input Events

All user interactions POST to `/input` and are forwarded to Claude as channel events.

### Format Claude receives

Events arrive as `<channel>` tags with metadata attributes:

```xml
<channel source="agent-canvas" event="form_submit" component_id="config-form">
{"env": "staging", "run-tests": true}
</channel>
```

### Event types

| Event | Trigger | Payload |
|---|---|---|
| `form_submit` | Form submission | `componentId`, `data: {fieldId: value}` |
| `custom` | Any element with `data-input-event` attribute | `componentId`, `eventName`, `data` |

The `custom` event is the general-purpose mechanism for `html` components. Any element with a `data-input-event` attribute becomes interactive — clicks POST to `/input` with the event name and parent component ID.

The `/input` endpoint returns `202 Accepted` immediately. It never blocks waiting for Claude to respond (see [why doc — no blocking input model](./agent-canvas-why.md#why-no-blocking-input-model)).

---

## Contract 3: HTTP Endpoints

| Route | Method | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `/` | GET | Serves the browser page (HTML + inline JS) |
| `/events` | GET | SSE stream — pushes rendered HTML on state change |
| `/input` | POST | Receives user interaction events from browser |
| `/state` | GET | Returns current `ui-state.json` as JSON (for initial page load and SSE reconnection) |
| `/files/*` | GET | Serves local files by absolute path |

### File serving

`/files/` serves any file from the local filesystem by absolute path:

```
/files/home/josh/images/exercises/squat.png  →  /home/josh/images/exercises/squat.png
```

In a state file, Claude references local files like:

```json
{"id": "demo", "type": "markdown", "content": "![Squat](/files/home/josh/images/squat.png)"}
```

Same trust model as the rest of the server — the security boundary is the network interface, not the file path (see [why doc](./agent-canvas-why.md#why-localhost-only-no-authentication)).

