## MCP Channel Contract

The plugin satisfies the Claude Code channel protocol using `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`:

```typescript
import { Server } from '@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/index.js'
import { StdioServerTransport } from '@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio.js'

const mcp = new Server(
  { name: 'agent-canvas', version: '0.0.1' },
  {
    capabilities: {
      experimental: { 'claude/channel': {} }
    },
    instructions: 'You have a live browser UI. Edit .canvas/ui-state.json to update it.'
  }
)

await mcp.connect(new StdioServerTransport())
```

Push browser input to Claude as channel notifications:

```typescript
await mcp.notification({
  method: 'notifications/claude/channel',
  params: {
    content: 'User clicked approve on approval card',
    meta: {
      event: 'custom',
      component_id: 'approval',
      event_name: 'approve'
    }
  }
})
```

Claude receives this as:
```xml
<channel source="agent-canvas" event="custom" component_id="approval" event_name="approve">
User clicked approve on approval card
</channel>
```

The `instructions` field is added to Claude's system prompt, giving it baseline awareness of the UI without requiring a skill or CLAUDE.md snippet.

